   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">A Program Manager or a Program Analyst or any user who has permission to create a program can create or manage the program from the contract or from a stand-alone program. Billing Programs are associated with agreements and managed as part of the agreement life cycle. Programs are associated with an agreement. When agreements are activated, programs are activated.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Agreement life cycle statuses supported in conjunction with the program are as follows:</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Agreement Status</b>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <table class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col3" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Status</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Transition</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Request</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">New Agreement.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">In Amendment</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">From Activated</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Programs are amended independently from Agreements.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Activated</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">From Request or after Amendment</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">When the Agreement is Activated/Approved the Program is Activated.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Terminated</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">From Activated</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Is manually set on the agreement. The versioned (original) Agreement status. Status Category is set to Superseded.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Cancel</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">From In Amendment </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">When the agreement is In Amendment, it can be canceled. The In Amendment version is deleted and the agreement Being Amended is re-activated along with originally activated programs.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">When you create a program from an agreement, the program will inherit all the above <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Status</b> from the Agreement alongside, <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Account</b>, <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Start Date </b>and<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> End Date</b>. For example, if a user performs <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Generate</b> action and the Status category is <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Request,</b> the program inherits the same Status as <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Request</b> from the Contract.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">As soon as the contract is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Activate</b> action, the system will automatically update the Status of a Program to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Activated.</b>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">After the Contract is activated and the Program is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">In Effect/Activated</b> status, a user cannot edit the attributes.</p>
      <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Only <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Amending Changes</b> (like <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Add Participants</b>) are allowed on the contract.</p>
      </note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Programs have their own statuses which are managed through the Agreement Life Cycle and through jobs that are scheduled as needed.</p>
